				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">heres my story:
<br />

<br />
i was playing my sk in poi and i had a pet up.  well i was ma and there were 3 other melees with me.  instead of fighting behind the mob, they were right in front, side by side.  i was keeping all the aggro but i noticed that their hp was going down.  of course u know what this means, riposte dmg.  so being the brainy ogre i am, i told them to hit the mobs from the back and they did.  and guess what, they no longer recieved any dmg.  as for my pet, i cant very well tell him to hit from the back so he stayed by my side.  and beside, through out the whole fight, not 1 % of his hp went down.  so this leaves me to the conclusion that pets dont get riposte dmg AT ALL.  i was fighting in poi for 3+ hours with my pet next time and not once did his hp go down and yes he was doign dmg since i had my pet attack showing (for those who would undoubtley say "but he's a grennie!!).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
