				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pets haven't taken ANY riposte damage since that patch.  And yes, when you reach 10+hrs of fighting mobs from the front, that is conclusive.  When a mob hits for 2k, before the pet changes it had the avoidance of a brick, and the AC of a druid, a single riposte would be EASILY noticed.  I can say with certainty that except for enraging, my pet has not taken a riposte since that change went live.  And let me be clear, your pet will miss his attack because the mob riposted, but the mob will not take a swing at your pet from that riposte.
<br />
Kopla</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
