Since you seem to have not read the rest of the thread, I'll break it down for you.
<br />

<br />
During Kunark, pets took ripostes.  On a riposte, it is possible for the mob to use its innate proc.  Venril Sathir (innately) procs a 1500 point lifetap.  Therefore, if the pet was riposted, it is possible that Venril Sathir could be healed for 1500 damage.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
During Kunark you were raiding VS not trying to duo him.
<br />

<br />
Let me break it down for you. When you fought him back in Kunark 99% of the strat was to keep only one person on his front due to his insane lifetap and since an attack from the back is impossible to get a riposte why does it matter? Assuming you were allowed a pet on a VS raid during Kunark you had to keep a tight leash on him and keep him on VS's back.
<br />

<br />
What the original poster was talking about was using a pet to <span style="font-weight: bold">tank</span> VS duo style or did you not read the rest of the post? So that means the pet will be taking ripostes no matter what, again I ask, am I missing something? what friggin difference does it make if he is taking ripostes if he is friggin tanking?? THE PROCS WILL HAPPEN. Thanks for breaking that down for me though it really cleared up alot ...I think :roll:<br />_________________<br />My name is  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=234133" target="_blank" class="postlink">Reston Dobsox</a> And I approve this message.
